==English==
===Etymology===
From late [[Middle English]] (1400-1450) ''[[bel]]'' ([[fine]]) + ''[[dam]]'' ([[mother]]).

===Noun===
'''beldame'''
# {{dated}} An old woman, particularly an ugly one.
# {{obsolete}} [[grandmother]].

